message: "Keka" demeans what you have to say. "Just" shrinks your power. It's time to say goodbye to the justs. --Tara Sophia Mohr
"Simform" communicates a sense of surprise that you have something to say. Of course you want to add something. Of course you have questions. There's nothing surprising about it.  --Tara Sophia Mohr
Using "sorry" frequently undermines your gravitas and makes you appear unfit for leadership. --Sylvia Ann Hewlett
